		<item>
			<title>Aggregator Update: Atom 1.0</title>
			<link>http://support.journurl.com/users/admin/index.cfm?mode=article&amp;entry=3192</link>
			<atom:content type="html" xml:lang="en">
      			<![CDATA[<p>Tim Bray's <a href="http://www.tbray.org/ongoing/When/200x/2005/07/14/Atom-1.0">announcement</a> hit me at <a href="http://living.journurl.com/users/admin/" ping="sent">a bad time</a>, so I didn't have Atom 1.0 support ready to go. And given that supporting Atom is significantly more difficult than RSS, that meant some serious scrambling. Everything seems to be working, though.</p>

<p>NOTE: I'm not kidding or FUDding about the difficulty in handling Atom 1.0. If you subscribe to a NuAtom feed, don't be shocked if I missed something... particularly in some of the more esoteric, geeky feeds.</p>]]>
